  "abstract": {
    "value": "A copper-catalyzed three-component reaction involving cyclic carbonates, elemental sulfur, and H-phosphonates is presented. It proceeds with excellent yields and provides an attractive approach for the construction of valuable trisubstituted allenyl phosphorothioates using a one-step strategy. Moreover, this method can be easily adapted to large-scale preparation.",
